root_causes: The column-flag variable flt_A1x1 is deleted before the OE (A1x1_9_other) checks are executed, so the OE checks reference a non-existent variable and will not run as intended.
The OE requirement check uses 'A1x1_9 > 0' and does not exclude special codes (97, 98, 99). This will incorrectly require A1x1_9_other when A1x1_9 contains a special-code value.
instructions: Do not delete flt_A1x1 before performing the OE checks. Move the 'del var ... flt_A1x1' statement to after the OE open-text checks (after both OE selection/list commands), or avoid deleting flt_A1x1 entirely until all checks complete.

Change the OE-required condition to exclude special codes. Replace the condition 'not missing(A1x1_9) and A1x1_9 > 0' with a check that the response is a positive numeric count and not a special code, e.g. 'not missing(A1x1_9) and A1x1_9 > 0 and A1x1_9 < 97' (or 'A1x1_9 in (1 thru 96)') so A1x1_9_other is only required for genuine numeric counts.

Ensure the OE-negative-case check (flagging A1x1_9_other present while count is missing/zero) similarly uses the column-flag (flt_A1x1) that is not deleted and considers special codes acceptable (i.e., do not flag when A1x1_9 is a special code).

root_causes: V-variable mapping uses '< 97' to decide which cell values to include in the numeric sum. This will exclude any legitimate numeric entries >= 97 (e.g. 100) from the sum instead of excluding only the special codes 97, 98, 99.
Sum-mapping logic is inconsistent with per-cell validation: per-cell allows 0..999 (including values >=97), but v-variable mapping excludes values >=97.
instructions: Change each v-variable assignment to exclude only the special codes (97,98,99) rather than excluding all values >=97. For example: compute A1x2_51_v = 0. if not missing(A1x2_51) and not (A1x2_51 in (97,98,99)) A1x2_51_v = A1x2_51.
Apply the same change to all v-variable blocks (A1x2_1_v, A1x2_52_v, A1x2_54_v, A1x2_53_v, A1x2_7_v, A1x2_2_v, A1x2_3_v, A1x2_4_v, A1x2_56_v, A1x2_5_v, A1x2_6_v, A1x2_8_v, A1x2_9_v).
Keep the per-cell validation (range 0..999 or in (97,98,99)) as-is so that numeric values up to 999 are accepted and only codes 97/98/99 are treated as special and excluded from the sum.
